title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare 1 of 25 Original NSG Navy Seal Grey Sage Int'l International Dot Matrix M14 MK-14 Stock
postcontent:
Very rare stock. Only 25 made. 	

1 of 25 Original NSG (Navy Seal Grey)Sage Int'l Dot Matrix Hand Engraved Logo EBR MK14 M14 Stock. 

The butt pad of this stock has a plastic plate in it that is broken and the butt pad will not stay mounted to the stock. The stock itself is not damaged. You will also receive the butt pad plus the 3 screws required to mount the stock to the gun. 

The story isn't 100% clear but there were 25 stocks made by Sage Int'l around 2004 that were similar to the civilian models, which were anodized black at the time not grey. The NSG Dot Matix stock seems to be a variant of the the civilian stock and some of the differences are that the NSG Dot Matix stock was anodized grey which, at the time, only the military versions were anodized grey, there were possibly some extra cuts made to the stock which lightened the stock and the rear of the stock was beefed up by machining it instead of welding it like the black civilians models were at the time. There were 25 of these stocks made but before the company logo could be machine engraved the stocks were pulled from the line. Apparently Sage was going to toss the stocks but last minute decided to hand engrave the logo and sold the lot to Clyde Armory and from there the first ever Navy Seal Grey stocks were sold to the public. It seems that some believe the front end of this stock was shortened from 13" to 11.25" and that is not true. The Dot Matrix stocks still retains the full 13" length at the front of the stock. The stock is referred to as the "Dot Matrix" style because of the hand engraved information on the side of the stock. 

I am willing to ship this stock. Payment via certified check or paypal or cash in person only. Payment must clear before I will ship the item. 

$150 includes insurance and shipping via Fedex or UPS ground only. 

Thanks for looking. 

Call, text or email with any questions or concerns.

title: For Sale/Trade:  HK Mark 23
postcontent:
The HK Mark 23 Caliber .45 ACP pistol gives shooters match grade accuracy equal to that of the finest custom made handguns — yet exceeds the most stringent operational requirements ever demanded of a combat handgun.

The Mark 23 provides this accuracy without the need for hand-fitted parts common in custom-built match pistols costing thousands of dollars more.

One of the most thoroughly tested handguns in history, the MK23/Mark 23 project originated in 1991 when HK began development for the U.S. Special Operations Command, the organization that directs the activities of America's most elite military units, including the Navy SEALs and the Army Special Forces.

On May 1, 1996, the first HK MK 23 pistols were delivered to the U.S. Special Operations Command for operational deployment, making the MK 23 the first caliber .45 ACP pistol to enter American military service since the venerable Government Model 1911A1.

During testing, MK 23 pistols met the most stringent operational and accuracy requirements ever demanded of a combat handgun. Endurance testing demonstrated a service life of over 30,000 rounds of +P ammunition. To meet the reliability requirement, the pistol had to demonstrate a minimum of 2,000 mean rounds between stoppages (MRBS) with both M1911 ball and +P ammunition. All pistols exceeded the 2000 MRBS with an average of 6000 MRBS. In more than 450 accuracy test firings from a precision firing fixture at 25 meters, MK 23 pistols far exceeded the government requirement, averaging 1.44 inches, with 65 groups of less than one inch. There were four groups of .5 inches, with 5 rounds going through the same hole!

title: For Sale:  XD Compact .45 ACP + factory accessories
postcontent:
So here's the story of this fine weapon.  It was the manufacturer's salesman show piece.  After it's show duty, the weapon was returned to the factory for reconditioning [my understanding of that process is that is was COMPLETELY disassembled, inspected, cleaned and reassembled as if it were a brand new unit].  I have owned it four years since & put (maybe) a couple hundred rounds through it.
I've used it as a personal defense-carry weapon.  I recently decided that I want to switch to a 40 caliber.  As the XD reputation stands, I have had no issues with this firearm!
I took it into the new mega retailer that moved into town.  They took it in the back for inspection and offered 60% of the $499 that they would resell it for.  That is where I came up with my fair market price of $450.
You can expect that the weapon in great shape, with the original accessory case & accessories.  They include: 
(1) Case
(2) 13 + 1 round magazines
(1) XD (Springfield) dual magazine holster
